---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteUrl = (Astro.site?.toString() ?? import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_URL ?? "https://pricingnest.com").replace(/\/$/, "");
const canonical = new URL(Astro.url.pathname, siteUrl).toString();
const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  name: siteName,
  url: canonical
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="PricingNest | SaaS Pricing Models, Cost Calculators, and Unit Economics Guides"
  description="Transparent SaaS pricing calculators, cost models, and practical guides for pricing teams, founders, finance, and product operators."
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>SaaS Pricing Models You Can Explain</h1>
    <p>
      {siteName} helps SaaS teams model pricing, cost recovery, and unit economics with transparent formulas, practical
      examples, and shareable calculator outputs. The goal is not to replace finance judgment. It is to make assumptions
      explicit so pricing decisions are easier to review and defend.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/saas-pricing/">Open the toolkit</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/about/">Read the methodology</a>
    </div>
    <div class="pill-row" aria-label="Highlights">
      <span class="pill">Transparent formulas</span>
      <span class="pill">Shareable links</span>
      <span class="pill">Worked examples</span>
      <span class="pill">CSV export</span>
      <span class="pill">No hidden vendor feed</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <h2>Four core pricing workflows</h2>
    <p class="muted">Start with one primary calculator path and only the retained support that helps you make the next decision.</p>
    <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-top: 0.9rem;">
      <div class="feature col6">
        <h3>Price API usage without hiding packaging risk</h3>
        <ol class="list">
          <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">Model the public API rate first</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/api-cost-estimation/">Check where cost estimation turns into packaging structure</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/api-call/">Define the billable event buyers will estimate</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/rate-limit/">Decide whether throughput stays hidden or becomes visible packaging</a></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="feature col6">
        <h3>Turn storage cost into an honest buyer-facing price</h3>
        <ol class="list">
          <li><a href="/saas-pricing/storage-cost-calculator/">Model storage economics before publishing the rate</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/storage-costs-and-pricing/">Decide when GB-month alone stops being enough</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/gb-month/">Keep the buyer-facing storage unit clear</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/minimum-commitment/">Add a commercial floor only when the variable model needs one</a></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="feature col6">
        <h3>Set a usage price without creating bill shock</h3>
        <ol class="list">
          <li><a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Model a baseline price per unit</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/value-metric-selection/">Choose a value metric your buyers understand</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/usage-based-pricing-examples/">Decide when the raw unit price needs tiers, included usage, or a floor</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/usage-based-pricing/">Keep the billing model tied to a clear usage concept</a></li>
          <li><a href="/glossary/overage/">Make the paid escalation path visible before buyers hit it</a></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="feature col6">
        <h3>Back into compute pricing before one monthly rate hides the real workload shape</h3>
        <ol class="list">
          <li><a href="/saas-pricing/compute-cost-estimator/">Estimate compute pricing</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/saas-gross-margin-targets/">Set a margin range before publishing the price</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/compute-cost-modeling/">Decide when a compute floor should become a commitment or heavier packaging structure</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/minimum-commitment-model/">Protect the commercial floor before heavier workloads distort the same public rate</a></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Secondary pricing checks</h3>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><a href="/saas-pricing/annual-discount-calculator/">Check annual discount tradeoffs after the core pricing structure is clear</a></li>
      <li><a href="/saas-pricing/seat-vs-usage-pricing-comparison/">Compare packaging models once the primary usage path is understood</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <section class="card col8">
      <h2>Why Teams Use PricingNest</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        The site is built for founders, product managers, pricing operators, and finance partners who need a fast model
        they can explain to someone else. Each calculator is connected to a plain-English guide so the math and the
        decision context stay together.
      </p>

      <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="feature col6">
          <h3>Transparent by design</h3>
          <p>Inputs, formulas, assumptions, and outputs stay visible so teammates can challenge or refine the model.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col6">
          <h3>Built for real SaaS workflows</h3>
          <p>Use the tools for usage pricing, API packaging, annual discounts, and infrastructure cost recovery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col6">
          <h3>Easy to audit</h3>
          <p>Shareable links and CSV exports make it easier to document why a recommendation changed from one review to the next.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col6">
          <h3>Clear limitations</h3>
          <p>We call out where a model is simplified, what costs are excluded, and when you should validate with deeper financial analysis.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Four core calculators</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Price per unit calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">API cost calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/storage-cost-calculator/">Cost per GB calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/compute-cost-estimator/">Compute pricing calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Secondary pricing checks</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/annual-discount-calculator/">Annual discount calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/seat-vs-usage-pricing-comparison/">Seat vs usage comparison</a></li>
      </ul>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Trust and methodology</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/about/">How the models are built</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/pricing-page-trust-elements/">Pricing page trust elements</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/">Guide library</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/">Glossary of pricing terms</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact/">Send feedback or corrections</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <h2>How Teams Review Pricing With It</h2>
    <div class="kpi-grid" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
      <div class="kpi col3">
        <strong>Pricing review</strong>
        <span>Attach calculator outputs to internal proposals and stakeholder discussions.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="kpi col3">
        <strong>COGS sanity check</strong>
        <span>Back into required prices from unit costs and target gross margin.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="kpi col3">
        <strong>Model comparison</strong>
        <span>Compare seat vs usage at the same workload to avoid surprises.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="kpi col3">
        <strong>Shared assumptions</strong>
        <span>Send pre-filled links so product, finance, and sales work from the same model.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
